296	
297	\textbf{Question Length vs Score.}  
298	Comparing Human-authored questions with o3 reveals clear gaps in quality. For short questions (\(<20\) characters), Human-authored ones are more than \textbf{2$\times$ richer} in quality (effort + evidence + grounding) than those from o3. The largest gap is in grounding, where Humans outperform o3 by over \textbf{10$\times$}. Effort is also substantially lower for o3, suggesting that even its concise questions often lack depth and framing.  
